Headlines.Headline: Jersey Central Power & Light: Power Restored to 99% of Affected Customers

PARAGRAPH.#text: MORRISTOWN, N.J.--Jersey Central Power & Light on Sunday said it has restored service to 99%of customers affected by Hurricane Sandy and the recent nor'easter. It said the majority of the 19,000 customers who remain without power should be returned to service by Sunday night. The restoration effort includes the 130,000 customers who were affected by the nor'easter, it said. Jersey Central Power & Light is a unit of FirstEnergy Corp. FE. About 30,000 customers on the barrier islands and in shoreline communities can't be restored to service at this time due to massive infrastructure damage in those areas, the company said, adding that it is working with local, state and federal officials to develop a full recovery plan for those areas.

gas prices to rise sharply during the next two years as new pipelines come
into service.
